Fisker Inc. is an American automotive company founded in 2016 by Henrik Fisker and his wife Geeta Gupta Fisker. It is known for cars like Austin Martin DB9. They aimed to create premium SUVs(Sports Utility Vehicles) targeting the luxury car market. Fisker cars beat Tesla cars on range but not charging.
In 2023 they managed to produce 10,193 fisker ocean model cars but could only deliver 4,929 cars. In June 2025 they have filled for bankcruptcy Chapter 11 after having financial issues and production delays.
After declaring bankcruptcy there can be many possibilities:
1. Either another company can buy Fisker Inc.
2. They company can restructure its business model to become financially stable.
3. The company can also be dissolved and its assests can be sold off.

ARENA is announcing $3.2 million for Amber Electric’s EV smart charging and vehicle-to-grid trial.

The Australian-first residential trial will show new ways of increasing value by reducing costs for consumers in the renewable energy transition.

The funding supports software development and installation of 150 chargers in participant homes. This includes electric vehicle smart chargers and vehicle-to-grid charging to support the electricity network in times of constraint.

Decarbonising transport is a key priority for ARENA on the pathway to net zero emissions.

Learn more: https://arena.gov.au/news/batteries-on-wheels-unlocking-value-for-customers-through-smarter-charging/

Electric Vehicles and those who own them and think they're saving the planet. 
Most electric plants run on coal. The vehicles and machinery used to (mine the coal) use fuel.🤫 The coal is shipped to plants using fueled trucks or trains, which either use fuel or coal. 😵‍💫
The grids (electric companies) are asking people to conserve electricity due to system overloads, yet someone somewhere is pushing for more EVs. Not to mention the infrastructure costs to car manufacturers & gas stations (reported in the millions), which they're still awaiting on returns from said infrastructure upgrades. 
Economics 101 (it just doesn't make sense). 
This is a picture of a CAT 797, one of the most used mega trucks, found on coal mines. Basic fuel capacity is 550 gallons up to 1000 gallons, which they use 30 gallons/hour to run. So, in a normal 8 hour day, that's a minimum of 240 gallons a day. 
Explain again how EVs are good? 🤣
CAT 797 Specs:
https://www.cat.com/en_US/products/new/equipment/off-highway-trucks/mining-trucks/18093014.html

ARE YOU MAKING THE MOVE TO ELECTRIC?

In 2023, electric cars accounted for around 18% of all new car sales globally, with almost 14 million units sold. 95% of those sales occurred in Europe, China and the United States. 2023 EV sales were more than 6 times higher than in 2018.

The growth in EV sales has been remarkable. In 2020, there were 10 million EVs on the road, in 2023 there were 45 million. But sales need to stay remarkable.

By 2035, the International Energy Agency (IEA) says there will need to be 790 million EVs if we're to hit net zero by the middle of the century.

That implies growth in sales of 27% every single year.

#electricvehicles #iffivemillionpeople

Blaine Raddon from Salt Lake City reserved a Tesla Cybertruck but moved to an apartment with tight parking.

When he discovered the truck didn’t fit, he tried to return it. Tesla reminded him of their agreement prohibiting sales within the first year, with a $50,000 fine and a ban on future purchases. 

Despite feeling this is unfair, Raddon won’t challenge Tesla legally. Tesla hasn’t responded to his appeal, leaving him waiting for a resolution.

Tesla's Cybertruck may gain certification in international markets, including Europe and China, by 2025, according to Elon Musk. This shift requires design modifications to meet various safety standards. Currently, the focus is on ramping up production in North America, aiming for 2,500 units weekly by end of 2024. Global demand remains high, but cost and compliance challenges are significant.

Charging on the go, charging made easy 🔋 @chargepoint Use your Mercedes me connect app to find chargers in a few easy steps:

1. Select the navigation tab (bottom right corner).
2. The map will open on your current location.
3. Select “Charging Stations” to see all nearby stations.

💥 🚗 Charging Station Insights You Should Know 🚗 💥 
 
As electric vehicles (EVs) become increasingly popular, understanding how charging stations work is crucial. Here are some key features and common questions answered to help you get the most out of your EV charging experience:
 
Key Features:
🔒 Overcurrent Protection: If the external load exceeds the rated value by 15%, the system will automatically cut off the power.
 
🛑 Zero Current Shutdown: Once charging is complete and the current drops to 0.5A, the system will shut down automatically to prevent unnecessary power consumption. Additionally, there’s an "emergency stop button" in the charging station for safety.
 
Common Questions:
❓ Is the charging connector always live?
No, the charging connector is not live until it is properly connected and authenticated with the vehicle. Only then does it start supplying power.
 
❓ What if the charging station malfunctions?
Charging stations are equipped with several safety features:
 
📍Signal Guidance Function: Ensures the connection is stable before starting the charge. If the signal changes during charging, the output will be cut off within 80 milliseconds.
📍Dual Switch Mechanism: This physically isolates the charging circuit when not in use, enhancing safety.
❓ What should I do if charging fails to start?
If you can't start charging, ensure the vehicle is turned off (some models may need to be locked). Make sure the charging connector is securely connected and you hear the locking click. If issues persist, contact customer service for assistance.
 
❓ Does the current vary for different vehicles?
The output voltage and current of the charging station is based on the feedback from the vehicle's battery management system (BMS), and the charging station itself is not able to freely output voltage and current to the vehicle.
 
❓ Does frequent fast charging damage the battery?
During fast charging with a DC charger, the charging speed is fastest when the battery is between 20% and 80%. Above 90%, the charging power will be reduced accordingly. This reduction is set by the vehicle manufacturer to protect the battery and prevent damage. However, when charging between 95% and 100%, some virtual power may be produced.

It's official, I'm a Graduate Engineer!

Yesterday, I successfully defended my B.Eng project—an in-depth research on electric vehicles and their adaptability in our country.

I thank God for His grace and guidance throughout this challenging yet rewarding journey.

This achievement wouldn't have been possible without the immense gratitude I have for:

📌 My amazing parents, whose unwavering support and belief in me have been my rock.
📌 My incredible supervisor and project group members, for their expertise, collaboration, and countless late nights. Teamwork truly makes the dream work!
📌 Everyone who assisted in one way or another.

The research aims to:

📌 Advance theoretical knowledge on the adaptability and use of electric vehicles (EVs) in developing countries, particularly Nigeria, where empirical studies are lacking.

📌 Provide practical insights and recommendations for policymakers, stakeholders, and researchers to promote and support electric mobility in Nigeria, addressing technical, economic, social, and political challenges and opportunities.

📌 Contribute to environmental and health improvements by reducing air pollution and greenhouse gas emissions from the transport sector, major causes of mortality and morbidity in Nigeria.

📌 Inspire future research on EVs in Nigeria and other developing countries, opening new areas of investigation, research methodologies, and proposals.

I'm so excited to see what the future holds for this technology and for my engineering career!

Tesla has postponed Cybertruck deliveries due to an issue with the windshield wiper motor. The Cybertruck features the largest wiper of any consumer vehicle, making it a unique design challenge. Some owners reported problems, resulting in Tesla delaying deliveries for a week. This issue follows previous delays due to faulty accelerator pedals. Not all units are affected, but a recall might be necessary. Tesla has not yet released an official statement.

The Cybertruck stands out in its production approach with its exoskeleton design. Unlike traditional cars that use a separate chassis and body, the Cybertruck integrates the chassis and body into a single, durable shell. 

This exoskeleton is made from cold-rolled stainless steel, providing robustness and reducing the need for a separate frame. This innovative production method contributes to the Cybertruck’s distinctive appearance and enhanced durability compared to conventional vehicles.

🌟 Exploring Neta's Global Journey in Electric Vehicles! 🌟

🚘 Neta Auto - A Milestone in Global Expansion! 🚘

As the electric vehicle market rapidly expands worldwide, Neta Auto is gradually making a name for itself with innovative technology and outstanding performance on a global scale. As the flagship brand of Hozon New Energy Vehicles, Neta has not only achieved significant success in the Chinese market but also made a successful entry into international markets. In 2023, global deliveries exceeded 127,500 units, establishing its position as a leading Chinese manufacturer of new energy passenger vehicles.

🌍 Global Vision, Local Reach 🌍

To further expand its global market share, Neta has set a 2024 global sales target of 300,000 units, including 100,000 units for overseas markets. This goal covers 60 countries and expands sales networks in Southeast Asia, Europe, the Middle East, and emerging markets such as Africa and Latin America.

🏭 Localized Production, Market Expansion 🏭

Neta has established its first overseas production base in Thailand and plans to commence local production in Indonesia in 2024. Through partnerships with local collaborators, Neta aims to build high-quality smart electric vehicles to meet the growing market demand.

💡 Smart Technology, Green Mobility 💡

As advocates of smart electric vehicles, Neta is committed to bringing advanced technology to every corner of the globe, ensuring that every consumer can enjoy a high-quality and affordable electric vehicle lifestyle. Whether in the success in the Thai market or the prospects in Indonesia, Neta demonstrates its strong brand potential and broad market recognition.

🌱 Join us in witnessing every step of Neta's brilliance in the global electric vehicle market! 🌱

user/name: Ministry of Power, Energy & Mineral Resources, Bangladesh
text:
ওজোপাডিকো'র মাধ্যমে আজ থেকে দক্ষিণ-পশ্চিমাঞ্চলের ১ম বৈদ্যুতিক গাড়ির (EV) চার্জিং স্টেশনের যাত্রা শুরু হচ্ছে যশোরের খয়েরতলাতে। 

এই চার্জিং স্টেশন থেকে ফাস্ট চার্জিং প্রযুক্তি ব্যবহার করে একটি বৈদ্যুতিক গাড়ি ৪০ থেকে ৪৫ মিনিটে পুরোপুরি চার্জ করা সম্ভব হবে। পরিবেশবান্ধব ও জ্বালানি সাশ্রয়ী হওয়ায় এই প্রযুক্তির মাধ্যম্যে একদিকে যেমন পরিবেশ দূষন থেকে বাচবে আমাদের দেশ অন্য দিকে কমে যাবে পরিবহন ব্যায়। ডিজেলে এক লিটারে গাড়ি চলে ১০ কিলোমিটার। প্রতি কিলোমিটার খরচ পড়ে ১৩ টাকা। কিন্তু বৈদ্যুতিক চার্জে গাড়ি প্রতি কিলোমিটার আড়াই টাকার থেকে দুই টাকা ৯০ পয়সায় খরচ পড়বে।
ওজোপাডিকোর সহায়তায় আজ শুক্রবার বিদ্যুৎ জ্বালানি ও খনিজ সম্পদ মন্ত্রণালয়ের সিনিয়র সচিব মো: হাবিবুর রহমান এই ফাস্ট চার্জিং স্টেশন উদ্বোধন করেন। এ সময় তার সাথে উপস্থিত ছিলেন বিদ্যুৎ  বিভাগের অতিরিক্ত সচিব ও ওজোপাডিকো' র চেয়ারম্যান এস এম এনামুল কবির, বাংলাদেশ বিদ্যুৎ উন্নয়ন বোর্ডের চেয়ারম্যান মো: মাহবুবুর রহমান, ওজোপাডিকোর ব্যবস্থাপনা পরিচালক এ.এইচ.এম মহিউদ্দিন, নির্বাহী পরিচালক (অপারেশন) মোহা: শামছুল আলম, বিভিন্ন প্রধান প্রকোশলী, প্রকল্প পরিচালক মতিউর রহমানসহ আরো অনেকে।

এ ব্যাপারে প্রকল্প পরিচালক মতিউর রহমান বলেন, পৃথিবীর উন্নত দেশগুলোতে এখন বৈদ্যুতিক গাড়ি ব্যবহার করে। আমাদেরও ক্রমান্বয়ে সেদিকে যেতে হবে। ইলেকট্রিক্যাল ভেহিক্যাল চার্জিং গাইড লাইন অনুমোদন হয়েছে।

An Israeli company has found new value in discarded batteries from electric vehicles, installing them at charging stations as an energy storage facility used to replenish functioning EV power cells. 

Once batteries in electric vehicles can only be charged to 70 to 80 percent of their capacity, regulations worldwide state that they have to be replaced, Sparkion VP Marketing Elad Halperin tells NoCamels. 

And those discarded EV batteries, instead of being consigned to the scrap heap, are being snapped up by Sparkion from carmakers and fleet owners and used as a power source at electric vehicle charging stations. 

Sparkion says its solution combines sustainability and affordability, as the repurposed batteries still have about 80 percent of the capacity of their newer counterparts, but cost just 50 percent of the price.  Ultimately, he says, the vision of Sparkion’s founders was to be both a viable company and one that helps to mitigate environmental damage.

Announced via Twitter, the force highlighted the Cybertruck's modern aesthetics and advanced technology, making it a perfect fit for their tourist police unit.

This move aligns with Dubai's vision of integrating advanced electric vehicles into its transportation and security infrastructure.

📢 Exciting News for EV Owners in Germany! 🚗⚡️

By 2028, large petrol stations will be required to have fast charging points with a minimum capacity of 150 kWh. This initiative aims to add around 8,000 new fast charging points across the country, making it easier for more citizens to switch to electric vehicles. 

Key Highlights:
🔋 Mandatory Fast Charging Points for large petrol stations by 2028.
🔋 Target operators: Those owning at least 200 petrol stations.
🔋 Urban focus to encourage EV adoption in cities.
🔋 Germany's goal: One million public charging points by 2030.

This move aims to solve electric mobility's "chicken-and-egg problem" and promote a cleaner, more sustainable future. 🌍

"**Sustainable Living in California**: Embracing a Greener Future 🌿🌎

California is at the forefront of sustainable living, with residents and communities passionately embracing eco-friendly practices to protect our planet. From urban centers to rural areas, Californians are making significant strides in creating a greener, more sustainable future. Here are some inspiring initiatives, practical tips, and personal stories highlighting how Californians are leading the way in sustainability:

1. **Community Gardens**: Cities like Los Angeles and San Francisco are transforming vacant lots into vibrant community gardens, promoting local food production and reducing carbon footprints.
2. **Zero-Waste Lifestyles**: Many Californians are adopting zero-waste principles, reducing plastic use, and opting for reusable products. Meet Sarah, a San Diego resident who has managed to fit a year's worth of trash into a single mason jar!
3. **Renewable Energy**: Solar panels are a common sight on rooftops across the state. California’s commitment to renewable energy is evident, with many homes and businesses switching to solar power.
4. **Eco-Friendly Transportation**: From electric vehicles to extensive bike-sharing programs, Californians are prioritizing sustainable transportation options. Explore the stories of families who have ditched their cars for bikes and public transit.
5. **Sustainable Fashion**: Discover how local designers in places like Los Angeles are creating fashion lines using sustainable materials and ethical production methods.
6. **Water Conservation**: With its history of droughts, Californians have become experts in water conservation, implementing innovative techniques to reduce water usage in homes and gardens.
7. **Green Building**: Learn about the eco-friendly architectural marvels, such as green roofs and energy-efficient buildings, that are setting new standards in sustainable construction.
8. **Recycling and Composting**: Cities across California have robust recycling and composting programs, significantly reducing waste sent to landfills.
9. **Farmers' Markets**: Support for local agriculture is strong, with farmers' markets thriving statewide, providing fresh, organic produce directly from local farms.
10. **Wildlife Conservation**: Initiatives to protect California’s diverse wildlife are making a difference. Read about the efforts to preserve endangered species and restore natural habitats.

These stories and initiatives reflect a growing commitment to sustainability in California. Each small action contributes to a larger movement towards a healthier planet.

Join us on this journey towards a more sustainable future! Follow our page for more tips, stories, and inspiration from around the world. 🌍✨ #SustainableLiving #California #EcoFriendly #GreenInitiatives #ZeroWaste #RenewableEnergy #LocalFood #WaterConservation #GreenBuilding #SustainableFashion #Recycling #Composting #ElectricVehicles #BikeSharing #FarmersMarket #WildlifeConservation #UrbanGardens #SolarPower #EcoTips #FollowUs #SustainableFuture"

Many have told me na sobrang tipid sa gas ng Nissan Kicks hybrid vehicle. So, let's put it to the test. Tara po! Come with me and my family on a roadtrip from Metro Manila to Tagaytay and back with the #NissanKicks.

Honestly, I didn't realize how suuuuper efficient this hybrid vehicle is until I tried it myself! Check out this video to learn just how much.

This is an excellent pick for those aiming to reduce their carbon footprint, explore sustainable options, and ease into the realm of electric vehicles.

The Nissan Kicks is actually termed a “non-hybrid” due to its unique e-Power technology, which is quite different from conventional hybrid systems seen in other vehicles. The e-Power technology of Nissan allows the Kicks to operate more like an electric vehicle with the internal combustion engine serving primarily as a generator to charge the battery, rather than directly propelling the vehicle.

Visit your nearest Nissan dealership and schedule a test drive so you can see for yourselves. Promise, hindi ito hype lang. ☺️🚙💯👍🏼

The funds will likely boost local operations, including new EVs, charging stations, and battery packs, enhancing Hyundai's market position.

১০. প্রাইভেট কারের স্টিয়ারিং ব্যবহার করা হয়েছে।

Geely and Mercedes-Benz's joint venture, Smart, is set to launch the Smart #5 electric SUV. The vehicle, nearly the size of a Tesla Model Y, features four powertrain variants, including a 638 HP dual motor AWD. The Smart #5 boasts a sporty design with a range of up to 700 km on a 100 kWh battery. The SUV supports 800V architecture for rapid charging, achieving a full charge in just 15 minutes. Expected to debut in the fourth quarter, this release underscores Smart's commitment to high-performance electric vehicles.

‘THE KING LEOPOLD OF 2024 IS PAUL KAGAME’

Speaking on our recent Pan-African Attitude podcast, Kambale Musavuli, analyst at the Center for Research on the Congo-Kinshasa, argued Rwandan President Paul Kagame is a modern-day Belgian King Leopold II, who was known for maiming Congolese as he colonised the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) to exploit its natural resources.

@kambale, a Congolese native and one of the DRC’s leading cultural and political voices, told African Stream’s team on 22 April that Rwanda is the central transit hub of Congo’s mineral wealth, a fact that Kagame himself has admitted to. And, just as Leopold ruthlessly extracted Congo’s rubber to supply the United States’ booming automotive industry more than a century ago, Musavuli said Kagame ensures the West’s environmentally friendly transition by allowing the smuggling of Congolese minerals to power electric vehicles (EVs) that don’t emit greenhouse gases. According to UN reports, the smuggling business is an economic incentive Kigali uses to finance and arm the M23 militia group.

#TipTuesday - Did you know? Most of the time you should only charge an EV to 80% because charging rates slow down significantly past the 80% mark. Also, the long term health of your vehicle's battery is improved when kept below 100%. Fully charging your battery every so often doesn't cause an issue. But regularly charging to 100% will affect long-term battery health. Instead, the best way to extend EV battery life is by depleting it to 20% and then charging it up to 80%

"Rivian: Revolutionizing Electric Adventure Vehicles with Innovation and Sustainability"

Rivian is a pioneering American company in the electric vehicle (EV) market, focusing on adventure-ready and sustainable technology. Founded with a mission to preserve the natural world, Rivian develops electric trucks and SUVs that combine robust performance with innovative features.

The company's flagship models, the R1T pickup and R1S SUV, exemplify Rivian's commitment to performance and utility. Both vehicles utilize a quad-motor system delivering up to 750 horsepower and a 0-60 mph acceleration time of about 3 seconds. The R1T, in particular, boasts an impressive towing capacity of 11,000 pounds and features like a gear tunnel for additional storage and a camp kitchen that can be powered by the vehicle's battery 

Rivian's vehicles are built on a flexible skateboard platform, which houses the battery pack, drive units, and other critical components. This design not only enhances durability and off-road capabilities but also allows for significant storage space, including a front trunk and a versatile cargo area. The R1T and R1S are designed to handle a variety of terrains with features like high ground clearance and advanced all-wheel-drive systems 

In addition to their initial offerings, Rivian plans to expand its lineup with the R2 and R3 models, which will introduce new motor configurations and advanced autonomous driving capabilities. These models will also benefit from Rivian’s over-the-air software updates, ensuring continuous improvements and new features over time 

Rivian's manufacturing operations are primarily based in a 2.6-million-square-foot plant in Normal, Illinois, with additional development centers in Michigan, California, and the UK. This extensive infrastructure supports Rivian’s ambitious production plans, including the upcoming launch of the R2 series

Overall, Rivian is making significant strides in the EV market, blending cutting-edge technology with a strong emphasis on sustainability and adventure. For more information, you can visit their official website

This innovative solution aims to enhance EV charging infrastructure and ensure power availability in critical situations.

Just less than two months after the debut of the Smart Concept #5, images and specifications of the production #5 SUV have been "leaked".

According to filings submitted to China’s Ministry of Industry and Information Technology (MIIT), the production Smart #5 will come with 4 powertrains with RWD and AWD options.

The Smart #5 is said to produce up to 646 hp (metric), making it the most powerful Smart EV. Its batteries with capacities of over 100 kWh will also give the #5 up to 550 km (WLTP) of driving range.

Set to be the largest Smart vehicle ever, the #5 retains the concept's boxy shape, but with its ruggedness toned down, swapped with some sporty bits instead.

More info here: https://autobuzz.my/2024/06/14/leaked-smart-5-suv-4-powertrains-over-550km-range-to-debut-this-year/

What sets Rivian apart from other manufacturers is its commitment to adventure and sustainability. The company aims to combine high-performance electric vehicles with off-road capabilities. 

Currently, it offers only two models: R1T, an all-electric pickup truck, and R1S, an all-electric SUV. Both vehicles have an impressive battery range with the R1T offering up to 400 miles and the R1S up to 300 miles on a single charge.

In addition, Rivian is developing electric delivery vans for Amazon. It shows Rivian’s ambition to transform not just personal transportation but also logistics and delivery services.

Overall, Rivian represents the future of electric car innovation, so let’s keep an eye on their fast-growing industry. We are glad to be a part of their journey.

India is considering the introduction of the FAME-III scheme in the 2024 budget to promote electric vehicles. The Ministry of Heavy Industries (MHI) has submitted a comprehensive proposal for review. The scheme aims to boost EV adoption with a Rs 10,000 crore allocation, focusing on two-, three-, and four-wheelers. Key measures will ensure proper subsidy use and increase local production capacity, addressing previous abuse issues. This initiative is crucial for achieving India's EV30@30 vision, reducing carbon fuel reliance, and promoting green mobility.

🚦 Myth: There's a persistent belief that electric vehicles (EVs) can’t match the thrill and performance of Internal Combustion Engine (ICE) vehicles, often labeled as uninspiring on the road.

⚡ Fact: Buckle up and prepare for a reality check! Today's EVs are not just competing with; they're often outperforming their ICE counterparts in terms of speed and acceleration. Here’s why EVs are the new frontrunners on the fast track:

🚀 Instant Acceleration:
• EVs benefit from instant torque delivery—their electric motors allow them to accelerate from zero to full power immediately, providing a rapid response that ICE vehicles can rarely match. Models like the Tesla Model S Plaid sprint from 0 to 60 mph in less than 2 seconds, making it one of the quickest production cars in the world.

🏁 Engineered for Speed:
• Beyond just quick starts, many high-performance EVs are designed with cutting-edge aerodynamics and weight distribution that enhance their speed capabilities. Vehicles like the Porsche Taycan and Audi e-tron GT have proven their mettle on the racetrack, offering exhilarating performance that delights even the most ardent speed enthusiasts.

🔧 Technological Advancements:
• The integration of advanced technology not only supports performance but also ensures EVs maintain high speeds efficiently and safely. Features such as regenerative braking, dynamic traction control, and adaptive suspension systems contribute to a driving experience that’s both thrilling and innovative.

🔕 Silent but Swift:
• The quiet operation of EVs adds a unique aspect to their performance. The lack of engine noise does not mean a lack of power; rather, it offers a new, stealth-like dimension to high-speed travel, redefining what it means to drive a fast car.

🌍 Sustainable Speed:
• Driving a fast EV doesn’t just mean breaking speed records; it also means embracing sustainability. Combining high performance with zero emissions, EVs offer a guilt-free way to enjoy speed with minimal environmental impact.
Forget the outdated stereotypes; the new era of high-performance vehicles is electric. EVs are providing adrenaline-pumping speeds that are redefining expectations and proving that the future of fast cars is electrified.

Let’s celebrate the speed, innovation, and silence of electric vehicles as they race ahead of the curve!

Battery Technology is Revolutionizing the Future of Transportation!

Hey everyone! Have you ever wondered what powers our sleek and silent electric vehicles (EVs)? It’s all about the incredible advancements in battery technology! 🌟 

What's the Buzz About?

Lithium-ion batteries, the main type used in EVs, have improved significantly over the years. This progress has led to:
- Longer driving ranges 🚙
- Increased efficiency ⚡
- Greater durability 💪

These improvements mean EVs can now travel further on a single charge, making them more practical for daily use. But that's not all! Researchers are on a mission to develop even better batteries with higher energy density, allowing for more energy storage without adding weight. They're also working on faster charging capabilities, which is super exciting for all EV enthusiasts who want to spend less time plugged in and more time on the road! ⚙️🔧

Why Choose Electric?

Electric cars are not just about being eco-friendly (though that’s a HUGE plus 🌍). They also offer an exhilarating driving experience with:

- Instant torque for quick acceleration 🚀
- Smooth, seamless driving without gear shifts 🌊
- High performance that often rivals traditional sports cars 🏎️

Plus, the variety of EVs available now is astounding! From compact cars to SUVs, trucks, and even electric buses, there’s an EV for everyone. Major automakers are investing heavily in EV technology, expanding their lineups, and introducing new models with advanced features. This means more choices for consumers and a big push towards a greener future. 🌿

EV vs Gas: The Better Choice?

In the debate of electric vs gas, EVs are coming out on top. They’re cheaper to run and maintain, and they don’t produce harmful emissions. While they might cost more upfront, they save money in the long run. And with the ever-improving battery technology and expanding charging networks, EVs are becoming more practical and convenient every day.

The Road Ahead

The future of transportation is electric! With continuous advancements in battery technology, EVs will only get better, promising even more thrilling driving experiences. Switching to an EV is a sensible step toward a more sustainable future. 🌟🚘

For more details on how battery technology is evolving and transforming the automotive industry, check out this blog article: https://i.mtr.cool/ikawhzrpgs

Let's drive into the future together! 🚗💚

#BMW AND RIMAC PARTNER FOR A SUSTAINABLE FUTURE IN EV INNOVATION

BMW has announced a strategic long-term partnership with Rimac Technology to co-develop and co-produce high-voltage battery technology for electric vehicles. This collaboration will leverage Rimac's high-performance electric expertise to boost BMW's electrification strategy, aiming for over half of their global vehicle sales to be electric by 2030.

BMW's commitment to sustainability is evident in this partnership. By combining BMW's extensive experience in battery and electric drive systems with Rimac's cutting-edge technology in high-voltage battery packs and e-axles, the two companies aim to accelerate the transition to electric mobility. This partnership not only enhances BMW's electric vehicle lineup but also sets a new standard for innovation in the automotive industry.

Rimac, known for its high-performance electric hypercars, brings a wealth of knowledge and technological prowess to the table. The collaboration is expected to produce highly efficient, durable, and customizable battery systems, significantly improving the performance and range of BMW's future electric vehicles.

This strategic move aligns with BMW's broader electrification goals, which include launching a wide range of electric models in the coming years. With advancements in battery technology, BMW aims to offer electric vehicles that meet the highest standards of performance and reliability, ensuring a sustainable and exciting driving experience for customers worldwide.

Here are just a few reasons why more and more companies are making the switch to EVs:

💷 Cost savings: EVs are cheaper to maintain and operate than traditional gas-powered vehicles, saving businesses money in the long run.

🌍 Sustainability: By choosing electric vehicles, businesses can reduce their carbon footprint and demonstrate a commitment to sustainability.

💡 Government incentives: Many governments offer tax credits or other incentives for businesses that invest in EVs, making the switch even more appealing.

💹 Improved public image: Show your customers and stakeholders that your business is committed to environmental responsibility and innovation by embracing the latest in electric vehicle technology.

1. **Speed**: The Q5 scooter can go at a nice speed ranging between 74 to 90 kilometers per hour,
2. ⁠allowing you to reach your destination quickly without hassle.

2. **Comfort**: It’s very comfortable because it has a dual suspension system that absorbs shocks from the road. The seat is also adjustable, so you can set it according to your height and comfort.

3. **Practicality**: It is easy to use and practical for daily commuting. It’s not heavy and can be folded and carried easily, so if you want to store it at home or the office, it’s no problem.

4. **Battery Power**: Its battery is strong and allows you to travel long distances up to 25-35 kilometers on a single charge, depending on conditions such as weight and driving speed.

5. **Additional Features**: It has nice features like front and rear LED lights for safety when riding at night, and a display screen that shows speed, battery level, and distance traveled.

Q1 2024 ZEV sales in Canada: 11.3% (StatsCan)🎉
The surge in ZEV sales during Q1 2024 showcases an impressive upward trend in Canada's adoption of EVs. 🚗
⚡ With a 31% increase in the sales percentage and a remarkable 53% jump in absolute sales compared to Q1 2023, it's clear that the movement towards sustainable transportation is gaining momentum.
 🌍📈 This growth translates to 46,744 ZEVs sold in Q1 2024, up from 30,555 in the same period last year.
Most of these sales were BEVs, accounting for 73% of ZEV sales, while PHEVs comprised the remaining 27%. 
🔋🚘 The data speaks for itself: the future of transportation is electric. 🌱

🌟 What an incredible weekend at the Noosa EV Expo! 🌟

We were thrilled to showcase our cutting-edge electric vehicles, the Asiastar D11 vanand the Yutong D7E small coach, at this amazing event. The turnout was fantastic, and we were blown away by the enthusiasm and interest from the community.

From eco-conscious families to adventurous travelers looking for a sustainable way to explore, our vehicles attracted a diverse crowd. We were especially excited to meet many forward-thinking travelers eager to upgrade their transport to something more environmentally friendly.

Our Yutong D7E small coach received a lot of attention for its quiet, comfortable ride and eco-friendly benefits, making it perfect for community transport and longer journeys. Tesla CEO Elon Musk has announced that the company's in-car navigation system will soon include an 'Avoid Highways' feature. This announcement was made during a livestream on June 9 when a viewer inquired about the possibility. Musk's response, "Alright, sure," confirmed the upcoming addition. Tesla’s navigation system, already praised for its live traffic updates and seamless integration with Supercharging routes, will now offer more customization akin to features available in Apple Maps and Google Maps. 

Although no release date has been specified, it is anticipated that Tesla’s software team will roll out this feature in an upcoming update, continuing their trend of frequent and innovative enhancements.

text:
Green Li-ion has established the first commercial-scale recycling plant for lithium-ion batteries in Atoka, Oklahoma, closing the EV recycling loop with its “green hydrorejuvenation” technology. This plant processes discarded black mass from shredded batteries to produce battery-grade cathode precursor and other sustainable materials. With provisions from the Inflation Reduction Act and support from the Atoka City Industrial Development Authority, the plant will process 2 metric tons of black mass per day, reducing greenhouse gas emissions by up to 90% compared to traditional methods. It's a key step toward electrification and sustainable battery manufacturing.  #GreenEnergy #Sustainability #BatteryRecycling #ElectricVehicles #CleanTech #GreenLiion #EnvironmentalImpact #AtokaOK #InflationReductionAct 

Learn more: https://www.recyclingtoday.com/news/green-li-ion-battery-recycling-oklahoma-singapore-pcam-black-mass-lithium/

#Clarkson on the #ToyotaPrius ~ I don't agree with the conclusion or language. A friend bought an early #Prius & rightly views it as an important car which showed what was possible. It wasn't particularly green and quite tinny but technology has advanced greatly and will do further. 

That said, there's some truth in what #JeremyClarkson says viz the enormous cost of #mining and #transportation and #manufacturing and further transportation incurred in the process of #production of the Prius and all #ElectricVehicles (#EVs).

My problem lies with the claims and statistics made by #ClimateChange zealots - as opposed to more moderate people who nonetheless have reasonable, worthy concerns which I share and have for decades voiced myself. 

Why? Because none of the costs Clarkson (and others) mentions here are taken into account, nor the #emissions and #pollution from the #PowerStations creating the #energy they rely on to power #ElectricCars. That is plainly wrong but absolutely widespread within the #ClimateLobby, as is the cancelling not just of other voices calling for ALL the facts to be taken into account and publicised but the voices of many notable scientists also sceptical based on their own statistical studies.

I regard this as fundamentally wrong and dangerous. It's also an afront to #FreedomOfSpeech /#FreeSpeech, #democracy and #freedom itself. And it wouldn't be possible without the widespread active participation of #corporations who enable #CancelCulture because they #profit from such deceit. 

If you have to silence doubters and sceptics, including well informed experts, to 'win' or rather enforce your view instead of affording them the same platform you are afforded then it's a fair bet things are not entirely as they claim they are.

Furthermore it's the same with the madness of #GlobalTrade today where we see foodstuffs grown and flown all over the world to satiate the desire of consumers to eat whatever they want - right here, right now - regardless of the cost to the global #environment instead of growing and eating seasonal produce grown more locally as notable chefs prefer. Raspberries from South Africa in December, anyone? 

Nobody serious about climate change would ignore this stuff. It's highly UNscientific. We export manufacturing - AND jobs AND pollution - abroad to enable  deceitful, cynical politicians and environmentalist zealots to claim to be #green, regardless of the costs to #employment and the #economy in terms of our #BalanceOfTrade and regardless of the degradation of the environment both in other countries and globally.

That is a con. I don't think it's necessary either. We need politicians willing to tell the unvarnished truth and willing to demand of electorates that they stop acting like children, accept that living life and running national economies requires making choices and acknowledge what is and is not possible or even true. If you silence doubters and sceptics so that only your own view is allowed and publicised you have no right to expect people to believe or respect - or vote - for you.

Have you ever experienced charge anxiety? ⚡️
 
Charge anxiety is the uncertainty about whether an EV charger will be available at a charging station when drivers need it most. This is usually caused by unreliable chargers, such as chargers that are malfunctioning or without a sufficient amount of plugs available. ❌
 
One answer to charge anxiety is dynamic charging. 💡

Dynamic charging means that the available power on the site is distributed based on demand to optimize charging across multiple vehicles at one site.
 
As a result, queuing times are reduced, charging speed is maximized and the availability of chargers for EV drivers improves. 🙌 It also enables the installation of more plugs to an EV charging site 🔌

Want to learn more? Check out our blog post 'The benefits of choosing dynamic power for public EV charging sites': https://kempower.com/dynamic-power-for-public-ev-charging-sites/

This move signals a significant shift for Tesla, potentially influencing other Musk-led ventures and sparking calls for Texas to authorize direct sales of Tesla vehicles. The final decision on Musk's pay package still rests with the Delaware court, leaving ongoing legal battles.

Partnering with Drive Electric, we hosted a Sustainable Fleets event for customers and guests, bringing NZ’s electric vehicle industry to the Wellington region.

The audience received an e-mobility update from Deputy Chair Eric Pellicer from  Drive Electric. Letitia Still presented FleetPartners' work helping businesses transition their fleets to EVs including an interview with Sean Chia on ANZ Bank's fleet journey. A panel session of electrification experts closed out the event – thanks to Eric Pellicer from Drive Electric, Sean Chia from ANZ Bank, Jonny Parker from Thundergrid and Justin Green from FleetPartners. It was also great to have Barnardos, Z Energy and evnex join us for the evening. 

The event was lit up with a selection of the latest electric vehicles on display. Thanks to our valued dealers for providing the fantastic vehicles – Gazley Motor Group, Johnston Ebbett, Capital City Ford and Brendan Foot Motors.

I am delighted to share the remarkable achievement of my daughter, Mashael Kamran. She has not only completed her PhD on Investigating Environmentally Sustainable Pathways for Passenger Vehicle Fleet in the UK but has also made a significant contribution to the field of sustainability. Her research focuses on unlocking the environmental benefits of second life, recycling, and reusing retired lithium-ion electric vehicle batteries. This work holds immense value within the context of the co-evolution of the transportation and electricity sectors. Mashael’s dedication, expertise, and innovative approach have paved the way for a more sustainable future. 
So proud of your exceptional accomplishment, Dr. @mashael.kamran @oxfordbrookes @oxfordbrookesuni #Phd

From China to the UK and the USA, here are the top-selling electric vehicles (EVs) based on January 2024 registration data.

As the automotive industry continues to evolve, 2024 has marked a significant milestone in the journey towards sustainable transportation. This year, we have witnessed remarkable advancements in electric vehicle (EV) technology, leading to a surge in EV adoption worldwide.

The Tesla Model Y was the best-selling EV globally in the first half of 2024, topping sales in the major markets of China, the US, and Europe.

Chinese automakers like BYD and Wuling also had strong EV sales driven by affordable models.

In smaller markets like India, Brazil, and Vietnam, EV sales saw very high year-over-year growth rates of over 50%, albeit from a lower base. This indicates EVs are gaining momentum across diverse markets worldwide.

Stay tuned as we continue to explore the latest trends and innovations in the EV market.

What a weird new experience! First off, if you’re Lynn Park and your Cobra breaks down, you can just go pick another one. He’s got the best Cobra exchange policy in the business. 🤣 And second, the fact that hot-rodder Lynn really enjoys Sparky @thescorpionev is so funny! He had offered several times to let me drive it, and when we went back to get another car after the battery died in the 289, he said, “Which one do you want to drive? Let’s take Sparky!” He couldn’t wait to show me! It’s like an electric golf cart when you first get going, and you only hear the suspension creaking and tires rolling. We took it on the freeway, and Lynn tells me to slow down. I thought, uh oh. I’m in trouble. I had crept up a little past the speed limit and thought maybe he was uncomfortable. “Now slow way down….
